The paper deals with object detection and segmentation in aerial images and videos using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel multitask learning network, which involves training the network to perform two complementary tasks simultaneously, namely, segmenting vehicle regions and detecting semantic boundaries. This involves using techniques from machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the theoretical analysis of residual networks, which is a topic in robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper proposes a new data set for vehicle instance segmentation, which is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) research.
